    { "kind": 1, "languageId": "markdown", "value": "# UI Project Instructions", "output": [], "executionSummary": {} },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "## Introduction\n\nWelcome to the UI Project!\n\nThis project provides hands-on experience building a frontend on the C3 Agentic AI Platform. You'll work with real-world data and create a dynamic dashboard. \n\n**What You'll Build**:\n* **Routes**: Custom navigation paths with dynamic parameters.\n* **Pages**: A complete page with React and C3 AI's UI framework.\n* **Components**: Reusable UI components with real-world styling.\n* **API Calls**: Basic fetches to complex filtered queries and pagination.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "### Selecting the Correct Application\n\nC3 notebooks require a specific application. Once connected to your environment, use the **Select Application** button in the notebook's navigation bar to pick the application that contains your UI project quickstart.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "### Estimated Time\n\nThis lab will take approximately **2-3 hours** to complete.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "### Learning Objectives\n\nAt the end of this project, you will be able to:\n* Implement custom pages and routes.\n* Build styled React components.\n* Perform complex API calls.\n* Read from the Redux store.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "---\n\n## Project Overview\n\nIn this project, you transform a basic aviation management application into an interactive dashboard.\n\nThis project has five parts, each building on the last. You'll start by enabling navigation, then create a route, fetch live data, display metrics, and finally implement a memory-effective paginated table.\n\nEach activity is marked with a blue box containing step-by-step instructions that map directly to `/* TODO */` comments in your code. Follow along, complete each TODO, and finish the dashboard.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    { "kind": 1, "languageId": "markdown", "value": "---\n\n## Getting Started", "output": [], "executionSummary": {} },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Run the cell below to load time-series sensor measurement data. Loading usually takes 1-2 minutes:",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "javascript",
      "value": "DataGenerator.createSensorMeasurementData();",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Run the cell below to verify data is loaded into the aviation data model correctly:",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 2,
      "languageId": "javascript",
      "value": "DataGenerator.validateDataLoad();",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "The data model contains the following Types:\n* **Operation**: Missions and deployment operations.\n* **OperationAlert**: Alerts generated for an operation, capturing issues, warnings, or status changes tied to that mission.\n* **Base**: Installations where aircraft are stationed.\n* **Aircraft**: Individual planes in the fleet with status and location data.\n* **MaintenanceRecord**: Historical records of aircraft maintenance and repairs.\n* **WorkOrder**: Scheduled and ongoing maintenance tasks for aircraft.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "![Aviation Fleet ERD](./images/getting_started/ERD_V2_2.png)",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "---\n\n## Part 1: Add Navigation from the Landing Page to the `Base` Details Page\n\nUsers can see bases on the map, but navigation with the **View Details** button doesn't work. Let's fix it.\n\nIn this section, you'll complete the click-to-navigate functionality using Redux actions. When someone selects the **View Details** button on a `Base`, they'll be navigated to a dedicated `Base` details page.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"color: black;\">\n<h4><b>Activity 1.1: Dispatch the <code>\"GLOBAL_REDIRECT\"</code> Action</b></h4>\n\nStart this activity by navigating to <a href=\"../ui/c3/src/components/map/BasePopup.tsx\" style=\"color: blue;\">ui/c3/src/components/map/BasePopup.tsx</a>.\n\n**Instructions**:\n\n1. Open the `BasePopup.tsx` file.\n2. Locate the event handler `handleNavigateToBaseDetailsPage` and `TODO 1.1`.\n3. Complete the `dispatch` call by filling in two fields:\n    - `type`: Set to the type of action (i.e. `\"GLOBAL_REDIRECT\"`).\n    - `url`: Set to a JavaScript template string that uses `base.id` to build the URL: `/bases/<BASE_ID>`. If the `base.id` is `\"BASE-1\"`, then the URL would be `/bases/BASE-1`.\n\n**Hint**: The `Base` object is already available in the `BasePopup` component's props. Use `console.log()` to see the available fields.\n</div>",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "### Check Your Work\n\n**Expected Behavior**\n\nBy the end of this activity, you can:\n\n1. Click any `Base` marker on the map.\n2. In the popup, click **View Details**.\n3. The browser navigates to `/bases/{{baseId}}` (for example `/bases/BASE-1`).\n4. A **404 Not Found** page appears. This is expected for now; you'll fix this in section 2.\n5. Open Chrome DevTools → Console.\n6. At the top of the console, confirm the dispatched action matches:\n\n```js\n{\n    type: \"GLOBAL_REDIRECT\",\n    payload: {\n        url: \"/bases/BASE-1\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe `BASE-1` above should match the ID of the `Base` you clicked.\n\n**What You Should See**:",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "![404 Page Not Found Image (Part 1 Activity)](./images/part_1/404_page_not_found.png)",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "---\n\n## Part 2: Define the Route\n\nThe app currently navigates to a route that doesn't exist yet.\n\nIn this section, you'll define a new route for the `Base` details page.\n",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "<style>\n.thick-table table {\n  border-collapse: separate;\n  border-spacing: 0;\n  border: 2px solid black !important;\n  background-color: #f5f5f5;\n}\n\n.thick-table th,\n.thick-table td {\n  padding: 8px 10px !important;\n  border: 1px solid black;\n  font-size: 14px;\n}\n\n.thick-table th {\n  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);\n  font-weight: 600;\n}\n\n/* Alternating row colors */\n.thick-table tbody tr:nth-child(even) {\n  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.02);\n}\n\n.thick-table tbody tr:nth-child(odd) {\n  background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.8);\n}\n\n/* Ensure header row maintains its styling */\n.thick-table thead tr {\n  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05) !important;\n}\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"color: black;\">\n<h4><b>Activity 2.1: Create the <code>Base</code> Details Route</b></h4>\n\nStart this activity by navigating to <a href=\"../metadata/UiSdlRoute/UiRoute.csv\" style=\"color: blue;\">/metadata/UiSdlRoute/UiRoute.csv</a>.\n\n**Instructions**:\n\n1. Open the `UiRoute.csv` file\n2. Add a new row at the end of the file with the following values:\n\n<div class=\"thick-table\">\n\n| targetModuleName | targetPageName | name | urlPath | \n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Aircraft | BaseDetailsPage | /bases/{{baseId}} | /bases/{{baseId}}\n</div>",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "### Check Your Work\n\n**Expected Behavior**:\n\n1. Click on a `Base` marker on the map.\n2. Click the **View Details** button.\n3. The `Base` details page loads. The page will be stuck in a loading state until we complete the API call in section 3.\n\n**What You Should See**:\n</div>",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "![Loading Page Image (Part 2 Activity)](./images/part_2/loading_animation.png)",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "---\n\n## Part 3: Fetch the `Base` Data\n\nThe page is stuck in the loading animation since the `Base` data is empty.\n\nIn this section, you'll build out the page's data flow:\n1. Read the `Base` ID from the Redux store.\n2. Fetch that specific `Base`'s details from the backend.\n3. Display the data on your page.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "<style>\n  .code-block {\n    background: #000 !important;\n    color: #fff !important;\n    padding: 16px;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    margin: 12px 0;\n    white-space: pre;\n    overflow-x: auto;\n  }\n  .code-block code {\n    background: transparent !important; /* prevent double background */\n    color: inherit !important;\n    display: block;\n    padding: 0;\n  }\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"color: black;\">\n<h4><b>Activity 3.1: Read the Page Parameters from the Redux Store</b></h4>\n\nStart this activity by navigating to <a href=\"../ui/c3/src/customInstances/Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage.tsx\" style=\"color: blue;\">/ui/c3/src/customInstances/Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage.tsx</a>.\n\n**Instructions**:\n\n1. Open the file `Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage.tsx`.\n2. Navigate to `TODO 3.1`.\n3. Complete the `getIn()` method call by filling in the correct path.\n\n**Hint**: In the Redux store, the page parameters are stored in an object formatted like:\n\n<pre class=\"code-block\">\n<code>\n{\n    \"pageParams\": {\n        \"baseId\": \"BASE-1\"\n    }\n}\n</code>\n</pre>\n</div>",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Now that you have the `Base`'s ID from the Redux store, you'll use it to fetch all of the data.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "<style>\n  .code-block {\n    background: #000 !important;\n    color: #fff !important;\n    padding: 16px;\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    margin: 12px 0;\n    white-space: pre;\n    overflow-x: auto;\n  }\n  .code-block code {\n    background: transparent !important; /* prevent double background */\n    color: inherit !important;\n    display: block;\n    padding: 0;\n  }\n</style>\n\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"color: black;\">\n<h4><b>Activity 3.2: Retrieve and Filter the <code>Base</code> Data By ID</b></h4>\n\nStart this activity by navigating to <a href=\"../ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/BaseCRUD.ts\" style=\"color: blue;\">/ui/c3/src/components/CRUDMethods/BaseCRUD.ts</a>.\n\n**Instructions**:\n\n1. Open the file `BaseCRUD.ts`.\n2. Complete `TODO 3.2` in the `fetchBaseById` function:\n\n    i. Make a POST request to the endpoint `api/8/Base/fetch`.\n\n    - Use the `fetch()` API with method `POST`.\n    - Include headers: `{ 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }`.\n    - Pass a request body that filters the `Base` Types by ID.\n\n    **Hint**: Set the `filter` field to a string and JSON-stringify the body. Example:\n\n    <pre class=\"code-block\"><code>\n    {\n        ...,\n        body: JSON.stringify({ \n            filter: \"id == 'BASE-1'\" \n        })\n    }\n    </code></pre>\n\n    ii. Parse the response as JSON\n    \n    iii. Return the parsed data\n</div>",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "Next, we want to call the `fetchBaseById` function when the `BaseDetailsPage` component mounts to retrieve the `Base`'s data and store into state.",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "<div class=\"alert alert-info\" style=\"color: black;\">\n<h4><b>Activity 3.3: Trigger the API Call</b></h4>\n\nStart this activity by navigating to <a href=\"../ui/c3/src/customInstances/Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage.tsx\" style=\"color: blue;\">/ui/c3/src/customInstances/Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage.tsx</a>.\n\n**Instructions**:\n\n1. Open the file `Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage.tsx`. \n2. Import the function `fetchBaseById` from the file `BaseCRUD.ts` in `TODO 3.3.1`.\n3. Complete `TODO 3.3.2` in the `useEffect` hook:\n    - Call the function `fetchBaseById` with the `Base`'s ID as an argument. Use the ID retrieved from the Redux store in activity 3.1.\n    - Store the resulting `Base` JSON into the state `base`.\n</div>",
