    {
      "kind": 1,
      "languageId": "markdown",
      "value": "---\n\n## Grading\n\nYou’re ready to submit. Capture every screenshot with the browser URL bar visible.\n\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">\n⚠️ All screenshots must clearly show the page URL in the browser. ⚠️\n</div>\n\n<ol style=\"line-height: 1.6; padding-left: 20px;\">\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 20px;\">Create a folder named <code>screenshots</code> for all images.</li>\n\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\nHome: landing page. Save as <code>/screenshots/landing.png</code>.\n<img src=\"./images/grading/landing.png\" alt=\"Final Landing Page\" style=\"display:block; margin:16px auto 0; width:70%; max-width:800px;\">\n</li>\n\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\nBase details: click <b>View Details</b> to open <code>Aircraft.BaseDetailsPage</code>. Save as <code>/screenshots/base_details.png</code>.\n<img src=\"./images/grading/base_details.png\" alt=\"Base Details Page\" style=\"display:block; margin:16px auto 0; width:70%; max-width:800px;\">\n</li>\n\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\nOperations page (page 1): scroll to the bottom so the paginated table is visible. Save as <code>/screenshots/operations_paginated_table.png</code>.\n<img src=\"./images/grading/operations_paginated_table.png\" alt=\"Operations Table Page 1\" style=\"display:block; margin:16px auto 0; width:70%; max-width:800px;\">\n</li>\n\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\nOperations page (page 2): click <code>&gt;</code> to go to page 2 and capture again. Save as <code>/screenshots/operations_paginated_table_page_2.png</code>.\n<img src=\"./images/grading/operations_paginated_table_page_2.png\" alt=\"Operations Table Page 2\" style=\"display:block; margin:16px auto 0; width:70%; max-width:800px;\">\n</li>\n\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 24px;\">\nYou should have four screenshots in the `/screenshots` directory. This is the expected structure:\n<pre><code>/screenshots\n├── landing.png\n├── base_details.png\n├── operations_paginated_table.png\n└── operations_paginated_table_page_2.png\n</code></pre>\n\nFrom the parent directory that contains the `screenshots` folder, zip it with:\n- macOS/Linux: <code>zip -r submission.zip screenshots/</code><br>\n- Windows PowerShell: <code>Compress-Archive -Path .\\screenshots\\* -DestinationPath submission.zip</code><br>\n- Windows CMD: <code>powershell -Command \"Compress-Archive -Path .\\screenshots\\* -DestinationPath submission.zip\"</code>\n  </li>\n\n<li style=\"margin-bottom: 12px;\">Follow the next section’s submission steps to upload your ZIP for grading.</li>\n</ol>\n",
      "output": [],
      "executionSummary": {}
    },
